When building cross-platform apps with Flutter, you often need to share logic between your mobile and web implementations. To achieve this efficiently, consider using a monorepo strategy. Create a separate folder for shared code and define a pub package within it. Then, add the package to your mobile and web projects as dependencies. This way, you can manage shared logic in a central location, reducing code duplication and making maintenance easier. For example, create a pub package called `shared_logic` in a `lib/shared` folder:
```dart
// lib/shared/shared_logic/lib/shared_logic.dart
export 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
default_value<T>(T Function() factory) => factory();
```

